Let’s say a company runs multiple AWS projects:

AWS Account 1: "Production"

This account is for live customer applications.
It has multiple IAM users (e.g., admin-user, developer1, ops-team).
AWS Account 2: "Development"

This account is for testing and staging.
It has different IAM users for developers.
IAM Users in Each Account

admin-user (Full access to AWS services)
developer1 (Limited access, can modify applications but not billing)
ops-team (Access to monitoring tools only)
